panorama /ˌpænəˈrɑːmə, -ˈræmə/

(panoramas) 

1. N-COUNT A panorama is a view in which you can see a long way over a wide area of land, usually because you are on high ground. 全景; 远景 

例： Horton looked out over a panorama of fertile valleys and gentle hills. 霍顿眺望着那一片肥沃山谷和平缓山脉的景象。 

2. N-COUNT A panorama is a broad view of a state of affairs or of a constantly changing series of events. 概述; 全貌 

例： The play presents a panorama of the history of communism. 这出戏展现了共产主义历史的全貌。

</div>

